  "summary": "Moderate: zlib security update",
  "details": "The zlib packages provide a general-purpose lossless data compression library that is used by many different programs.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* zlib: a heap-based buffer over-read or buffer overflow in inflate in inflate.c via a large gzip header extra field (CVE-2022-37434)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
